etymologies: early 18th century: modern Latin, from constrict- ‘bound tightly together’, from the verb constringere (see constrain)

definitions: a snake that kills by coiling around its prey and asphyxiating it.

notes.text: Families Boidae and Pythonidae, and some members of other families (in particular Colubridae)

shortDefinitions: snake that kills by coiling round its prey and asphyxiating it

definitions: a muscle whose contraction narrows a vessel or passage.
shortDefinitions: muscle whose contraction narrows vessel or passage

definitions: each of the muscles which constrict the pharynx.
shortDefinitions: each of muscles which constrict pharynx
